# Tailwind CSS Usage in SolidJS + Vite

## 🎨 **Tailwind v3 Integration**

**CRITICAL**: This SolidJS + Vite application uses **Tailwind CSS v3** (not v4) with Modus Design System integration.

**Configuration**: Tailwind v3 with design system colors mapped in `tailwind.config.js` and custom utilities in `src/index.css`

## ❌ **FORBIDDEN: Generic Tailwind Colors**

### ❌ **Never Use Generic Tailwind Color Classes**

```tsx
// ❌ WRONG: Generic Tailwind color classes
class = "bg-blue-500 text-white border-gray-300";
class = "bg-red-400 text-yellow-200 border-green-500";
class = "bg-gray-100 text-black border-purple-300";
class = "bg-indigo-600 text-orange-100 border-pink-400";
```

### ❌ **Never Use Hardcoded Colors**

```tsx
// ❌ WRONG: Hardcoded colors
class="bg-[#ffffff] text-[#000000] border-[#e5e5e5]"
class="bg-[#3b82f6] text-[#ffffff] border-[#1d4ed8]"
style={{ backgroundColor: "#ffffff", color: "#000000" }}
```

### ❌ **Never Use Raw Modus Variables**

```tsx
// ❌ WRONG: Raw Modus CSS variables
class="bg-[var(--modus-wc-color-base-page)]"
class="text-[var(--modus-wc-color-base-content)]"
style={{ backgroundColor: "var(--modus-wc-color-base-page)" }}
```

